The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 New Delhi, June 26 (PTI): A court extended by 14 days the judicial custody of Madhuri Gupta, a diplomat who has been arrested for allegedly leaking classified information to Pakistani intelligence officials. Delhi police had arrested Gupta on April 22.          
	The police have not yet filed a chargesheet, which they have to do within 90 days. Gupta is facing the charge of violating the Official Secrets Act.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): Delhi will get the countrys first commercial waste-to-power plant, of 16 MW capacity, that will convert one third of the capitals garbage into electricity for six lakh homes.                  
	 Islamabad (PTI): Pakistan has said it will to set up a special corridor for Sikh pilgrims to visit the Gurdwara Kartarpur Sahib, only 3km from the international border. Indian Sikhs have been seeking the establishment of a passport- and visa-free passage between Dera Baba Nanak in India and Gurdwara Kartarpur Sahib.                  
	 Bhopal (PTI): The Madhya Pradesh government has decided to hike the salaries and allowances of the states judges and retired judicial officers on recommendations of the E. Padmanabhan committee. The government has decided to implement the committees recommendations from January 1, 2006.                  
	 Sivaganga (PTI): The forced marriage of a 16-year-old girl was stopped by social welfare department officials, who had been tipped off about the wedding. The girl was handed over to her parents on condition that she would be allowed to study as she wished.                                                                                                                                              
